,Recommended,429600,20597719,"Posted: 17 January, 2016",all,kiminoa,"Cute! I enjoyed the second game in this series, so grabbed this one when it became available on Steam. It has a bit less of the later bells and whistles, but the art is beautiful, the minigames interesting, and the voice acting is excellent. It's all very linear path, as expected of a casual point-and-click / hidden object game. I liked the creepy Puppet Master villain and the reveal that one of the scary puppets is an ally. The scene maps in the bonus content are pretty. B+ in the broader Artifex Mundi spectrum."
