76561198008914127,Not Recommended,429600,24756994,"Posted: 7 August, 2016",all,Wuzzerator,"This is a disappointing offering from Artiflex Mundi who are normally, in my opinion, the best Hidden Object games around. The story could be great but it's banal and the puzzles are often annoying. There are a number towards the end where you have to have looked at a sequence and remembered it, rather than it being written down in your notebook. That would be fine if you could leave the puzzle to check, but you can't! Instead you have to keep clicking things randomly in the hope that eventually you'll hit upon the correct sequence.Perhaps I'm being overly  harsh because of the high standards I expect from this developer, but I wouldn't recommend this when they have so many other excellent games."
