,Recommended,429600,29213977,Posted: 12 January,all,DocCovington,"I played the sequel first and was thrilled by it, so I thought, ""Let's give this puppet thing a try, even though I find puppets to be scary."" ;)Turns out it was the right decision. A solid release by a very talented studio. Loved the puzzles, the difficulty level ranged from simple to challenging, but mostly it was above average, thus made the game still feel challenging to a comforting extent.The story was okay, and I didn't feel bored a single second. Played through the whole game in two sessions, that's how much fun I had. Yes, there might be better ones (I highly recommend the sequel!), but this one is still worth buying -- it won't fail you, I promise.Apart from having this stretched to 16:9 (probably because it's not a new release), the engine is well programmed and the graphics quality good (although pixelated on higher resolutions). What's always important is that the UI and reaction time don't frustrate the player, and they certainly don't in this case. Everything works smoothly.Thumbs up for this one!"
