76561198105646429,Not Recommended,429600,21239804,"Posted: 15 February, 2016",all,Katzazi,"I love Artifex Mundi games. I am looking forward to them and buy them as a treat. They have so a high standard for games both on the story side as well as the minigames and how both is put together.Regrettably this game falls below their standards. The story as such has a lot of potential. But it remains shallow. While one normally is told some backgrounds and often enough there are some twists in the story, both is missing in this game. Anything that happens is more or less happening to you, even as it is meant to be, it does not feel as if anything is really happening because of what one did.And while there are some good mini-games they are seldom integrated well in the scenary. And the farther you go the longer the sequences of just repeating missing object mingames. Which would be ok, if they would not just pop up anywhere you look. If there would be something else to discover.Yes, there are some good ideas for rooms or scenery. But while I liked some of them I never had any idea why I would go there in the first place and why anybody would buils anything like this.It is really hard to vote on this. Because, would it not be an Artifex Mundi game I would say: Well good try for a game, not Artifex Mundi, but good approach. Try it to support the effort people have put into this.But it IS labeld as Artifex Mundi. And they have proven multiple times that they know how to do it much better then this.As there are so much better games there to play from Artifex Mundi, I would advise to buy one of those others. You will love those others. But if you have already played one of those excellent games you would regret to have buyed this game at full price.Try it if you have either played none or all other Artifex Mundi games and you get it on discount. But do not buy it if you are addicted to their games and have other options."
